description._content: Catalog #: 09_01617 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Harry Haw (on right) with Mrs. Ruth Giard Brookman, Art Stephenson, Roy Giard, Dewey Young and a Curtiss JN-4 ""Jenny"" aircraft in Desmet South Dakota, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
